# food-shortage-reaction
- I suppose we are eating @safe-food again.
- People are already trading it privately.
- The price doubled before lunch.
- Nobody knows when more will arrive.
- I should have bought some yesterday.
- That explains the argument near the counter.
- The substitutes are not fooling anyone.
- This station can move a reactor core but not a bag of flour.

# food-price-line
- The price of @priced-food is @price-amount at @canteen-place now. @food-price-reaction
- The price of @priced-food went up @price-change overnight. @food-price-reaction
- I paid @price-amount for @priced-food and they still charged extra for a clean spoon.
- Apparently, @canteen-place calls @priced-food a luxury item now. Yesterday it was staff lunch.
- You can buy @priced-food cheaper on @distant-place, and that includes the shuttle fare.

# priced-food
- a bowl of noodles
- one cup of coffee
- a ration sandwich
- a plate of dumplings
- a slice of cultured meat
- a piece of fresh fruit
- a mug of soup
- three algae crackers
- a breakfast tray
- a bottle of filtered water

# price-amount
- twelve credits
- half an hour's wages
- twenty station tokens
- more than my cabin's power bill
- six transit chits
- enough to buy a whole ration pack
- an insulting number of credits
- nearly twice yesterday's price

# price-change
- by three credits
- by almost half
- while I was standing in the queue
- for the third time this week
- without changing on the menu board
- the moment the passenger liner docked

# food-price-reaction
- At that price, it should come with a view.
- I am bringing lunch from home tomorrow.
- The tourists keep paying it, so it keeps rising.
- They blamed shipping costs, naturally.
- Even the cook looked embarrassed.
- I miss the days when bad food was at least cheap.
- Someone is making a fortune from hungry shift workers.
- I may learn to cook after all.

# food-service-line
- The queue at @canteen-place reaches @queue-landmark. @mild-ending
- At lunch, @food-worker forgot my order and gave me @wrong-order instead. I ate it anyway.
- They closed @canteen-place for @closure-reason just before my break. @annoyed-ending
- The ordering console recommended @prepared-food based on my medical record. That feels invasive.
- Today, @food-worker has been on shift for @worker-duration. I am not blaming them for anything.

