- I could have walked there faster, if space allowed it.
- Nobody at the desk knows anything.
- My luggage arrived before I did.
- The vending machine has become my closest friend.
- I have memorised every safety announcement.
- They gave us a meal voucher worth half a cup of coffee.
- I am beginning to understand why people own ships.

# transit-route-line
- Getting from @origin-place to @destination-place requires @route-complexity. @route-reaction
- The “direct” shuttle to @destination-place stops at @route-stop. Apparently that still counts as direct.
- I travelled @journey-distance to reach @station-name. @friendly-question
- The route map sends everyone through @route-stop, even when it is in the opposite direction.
- If you are going to @destination-place, change at @transfer-place, not where the signs tell you.

# route-complexity
- three transfers
- two shuttles and a cargo ferry
- an overnight wait
- a customs change halfway through
- one legal route and several better illegal ones
- a connection nobody has ever seen arrive
- crossing the station twice
- a trip through the old docking ring

